<div class="content_well top">
	<div class="the_hub_content_wrapper the_hub_article">
		<div class="the_hub_content">
		<a href="/category/the-hub/" class="header_link">
		<div class="the_hub_title_wrapper">
			<div class="the_hub_logo">
				<img src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/plugins/lb-content-widgets/img/lit-horn.svg">
			</div>
			<div class="the_hub_title">
				<h1>The Hub</h1>
			</div>
			<div class="the_hub_slogan">
				<h1>News, Notes, Talk</h1>
			</div>
		</div>
		</a>
		
				<div class="the_hub_item">
			<div class="banner_img">
				<a href="https://lithub.com/seven-books-to-scratch-that-pride-and-prejudice-itch/" title="Seven books to scratch that <em> Pride and Prejudice </em> itch.">
		    		<img src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/jane20austen20done20me20wrong-e1749052143165.jpg" alt="" class="post_ft entry_post"/>
		    	</a>
			</div>
			
			<div class="post_content">
				<h1 data-report-url="/seven-books-to-scratch-that-pride-and-prejudice-itch/"><a href="https://lithub.com/seven-books-to-scratch-that-pride-and-prejudice-itch/">Seven books to scratch that <em> Pride and Prejudice </em> itch.</a></h1>
				
				<div class="author_info">
					<div class="author_photo"><img src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/ESTRed-121-1-scaled-e1711474962955-100x100.jpg" width="100" height="100" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/ESTRed-121-1-scaled-e1711474962955-300x300.jpg 2x" alt="Brittany Allen" class="avatar avatar-100 wp-user-avatar wp-user-avatar-100 alignnone photo" /></div>
					<div class="author_name">By&nbsp;<a href="https://lithub.com/author/brittanyallen/" itemprop="url"><span itemprop="name">Brittany&nbsp;Allen</span></a></div>
					<div class="author_hr"><hr/></div>
					<div class="publish_date">June 4, 2025, 12:24pm</div>
				</div>
				
				<p>Jane is in the air lately. This year, Joe Wright&#8217;s <em>Pride and Prejudice</em> turns twenty, which is the same age Keira Knightley was when she starred as the cool girl&#8217;s Lizzy Bennet. A new feast of a French film, <a href="https://lithub.com/jane-austens-legacy-lives-on-in-rom-coms/"><em>Jane Austen Wrecked My Life</em>,</a> looks at all the ways the great lady may have destroyed our lives. And in other summer film news, Celine Song&#8217;s <em>The Materialists</em> promises to bring the P&amp;P-influenced rom-com back in a <em>big</em> way.</p>
<p>Unlike Keira, the real Lizzy was five and twenty and fast approaching burden-to-my-parents age when Mr. Darcy swept into her life. But real fans prefer to suspend disbelief. Speaking of, here&#8217;s a few novels to add to your summer TBR pile if you&#8217;re craving an Austen-y fix.</p>
<p><img fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="247328" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2025/mariam-rahmani-liquid-a-love-story/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Mariam-Rahmani-Liquid-A-Love-Story-.jpeg" data-orig-size="662,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Mariam Rahmani, Liquid- A Love Story" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Mariam Rahmani, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a class=&quot;external&quot; href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781643756509&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Liquid: A Love Story&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Sharanya Durvasala (Algonquin Books, March 11)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Mariam-Rahmani-Liquid-A-Love-Story--199x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Mariam-Rahmani-Liquid-A-Love-Story-.jpeg" class="size-medium wp-image-247328 aligncenter" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Mariam-Rahmani-Liquid-A-Love-Story--199x300.jpeg" alt="Mariam Rahmani, Liquid- A Love Story" width="199" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Mariam-Rahmani-Liquid-A-Love-Story--199x300.jpeg 199w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Mariam-Rahmani-Liquid-A-Love-Story--40x60.jpeg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Mariam-Rahmani-Liquid-A-Love-Story--33x50.jpeg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Mariam-Rahmani-Liquid-A-Love-Story-.jpeg 662w" sizes="(max-width: 199px) 100vw, 199px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Mariah Rahmani,</strong> <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781643756509" class="external" target="_blank"><em><strong>Liquid: A Love Story</strong></em></a></p>
<p style="text-align: left;">With its emphasis on the ruthless economic factors that affect one&#8217;s choice of mate, this debut novel scales the rom-com to late capitalist proportions. Here&#8217;s a truth universally experienced: a young scholar sets out to marry the richest man she can find. But sensibility gets in the way of good sense.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="255085" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/seven-books-to-scratch-that-pride-and-prejudice-itch/attachment/9780593134429/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/9780593134429.jpg" data-orig-size="292,450" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="9780593134429" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/9780593134429-195x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/9780593134429.jpg" class="size-medium wp-image-255085 aligncenter" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/9780593134429-195x300.jpg" alt="" width="195" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/9780593134429-195x300.jpg 195w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/9780593134429-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/9780593134429-32x50.jpg 32w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/9780593134429.jpg 292w" sizes="(max-width: 195px) 100vw, 195px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Jessie Redmon Faust, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9798890961341" class="external" target="_blank"><em>There is Confusion</em></a></strong></p>
<p>I&#8217;ve become an evangelist for this book from a star in the Harlem Renaissance cosmos, lately revived by a reprint and a Morgan Jerkins introduction. Following three ambitious siblings at the turn of the twentieth century, this is a zippy drawing room tale that ventures uptown. Expect much striving, and some satirical marriage plotting. <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780141197692" class="external" target="_blank"><em>Persuasion</em></a> people should take particular note.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="255090" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/seven-books-to-scratch-that-pride-and-prejudice-itch/a1lgexvc7jl-_ac_uf10001000_ql80_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/A1LGeXvC7jL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" data-orig-size="652,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="A1LGeXvC7jL._AC_UF1000,1000_QL80_" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/A1LGeXvC7jL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-196x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/A1LGeXvC7jL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" class="size-medium wp-image-255090 aligncenter" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/A1LGeXvC7jL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-196x300.jpg" alt="" width="196" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/A1LGeXvC7jL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-196x300.jpg 196w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/A1LGeXvC7jL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/A1LGeXvC7jL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/A1LGeXvC7jL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg 652w" sizes="(max-width: 196px) 100vw, 196px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Nancy Mitford, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780307740816" class="external" target="_blank"><em>The Pursuit of Love</em></a></strong></p>
<p>Mitford&#8217;s Nancy, an upper-crust lady of eccentric parentage making her way through interwar England, is a true romantic heroine. A little dippy, she makes a few miscalculations in her pursuit of love. But a motley cast of aesthetes and Communists show up to guide the quest. This novel, the first in a trilogy, pokes gentle fun at the aristocrat and all her unruly impulses. For <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780141439587" class="external" target="_blank">Emma</a></em> fans.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="255086" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/seven-books-to-scratch-that-pride-and-prejudice-itch/81ocj1ffajl-_ac_uf10001000_ql80_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/81OCj1ffAJL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" data-orig-size="662,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="81OCj1ffAJL._AC_UF1000,1000_QL80_" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/81OCj1ffAJL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-199x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/81OCj1ffAJL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" class="size-medium wp-image-255086 aligncenter" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/81OCj1ffAJL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-199x300.jpg" alt="" width="199" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/81OCj1ffAJL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-199x300.jpg 199w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/81OCj1ffAJL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/81OCj1ffAJL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/81OCj1ffAJL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg 662w" sizes="(max-width: 199px) 100vw, 199px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Emily Adrian, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780316584517" class="external" target="_blank"><em>Seduction Theory</em></a></strong></p>
<p>This <a href="https://lithub.com/22-novels-you-need-to-read-this-summer/">forthcoming-this-summer novel</a> is a gleefully constructed diagram of several affairs. Written in the form of an MFA thesis, the book offers a postmodern dissection of the ways power affects coupling partnerships. There&#8217;s an entanglement involving professors, graduate students, and department leaders that ends in a true Edwardian muddle. Extremely fun and incredibly itchy.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="255087" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/seven-books-to-scratch-that-pride-and-prejudice-itch/version-1-0-0-45/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/61kLR5nFkFL.jpg" data-orig-size="800,1200" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;Version 1.0.0&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;Version 1.0.0&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Version 1.0.0" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Version 1.0.0&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/61kLR5nFkFL-200x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/61kLR5nFkFL-683x1024.jpg" class="size-medium wp-image-255087" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/61kLR5nFkFL-200x300.jpg" alt="" width="200" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/61kLR5nFkFL-200x300.jpg 200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/61kLR5nFkFL-683x1024.jpg 683w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/61kLR5nFkFL-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/61kLR5nFkFL-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/61kLR5nFkFL-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/61kLR5nFkFL.jpg 800w" sizes="(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Patricia Park, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780143107941" class="external" target="_blank"><em>Re: Jane</em></a></strong></p>
<p>This 2016 novel is technically an homage to another classic—Bronte&#8217;s <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780141441146" class="external" target="_blank"><em>Jane Eyre</em></a>. But Park has a knack for echoing mannered 19th century conundrums. When <em>this</em> Jane, of Queens—an orphaned, hapa student of <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2019/11/02/opinion/sunday/nunchi.html" class="external" target="_blank"><i>nunchi</i></a>—accepts an au pair position with English professors, her world begins to open up in unexpected ways. A coming into self story befitting our time.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="255089" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/seven-books-to-scratch-that-pride-and-prejudice-itch/m-5/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/m.jpg" data-orig-size="768,1200" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="m" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/m-192x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/m-655x1024.jpg" class="size-medium wp-image-255089 aligncenter" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/m-192x300.jpg" alt="" width="192" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/m-192x300.jpg 192w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/m-655x1024.jpg 655w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/m-38x60.jpg 38w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/m-32x50.jpg 32w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/m.jpg 768w" sizes="(max-width: 192px) 100vw, 192px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Lily King, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780802160300" class="external" target="_blank"><em>The English Teacher</em></a></strong></p>
<p>I&#8217;ve been on a Lily King completist mission. I&#8217;m not sure I&#8217;ve ever seen this un-flashy architect miss. This early novel follows a mother and son whose lives are thrown into chaos when mom accepts a marriage proposal from a mysterious widower. Like <em>Re: Jane</em>, this book pays homage to another classic: Thomas Hardy&#8217;s <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781500488710" class="external" target="_blank"><em>Tess of the D&#8217;Urbervilles</em></a>. In that old fashion, the novel&#8217;s concerned with trauma, the compromises we make to pursue safety, and the joys of a life spent in letters.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="255088" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/seven-books-to-scratch-that-pride-and-prejudice-itch/51gyqrw8ezl-_ac_uf10001000_ql80_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/51GYQRW8EZL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" data-orig-size="644,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="51GYQRW8EZL._AC_UF1000,1000_QL80_" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/51GYQRW8EZL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-193x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/51GYQRW8EZL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-255088 aligncenter" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/51GYQRW8EZL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-193x300.jpg" alt="" width="193" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/51GYQRW8EZL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-193x300.jpg 193w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/51GYQRW8EZL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/51GYQRW8EZL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-32x50.jpg 32w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/51GYQRW8EZL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg 644w" sizes="(max-width: 193px) 100vw, 193px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Larry McMurtry, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780684853901" class="external" target="_blank">Terms of Endearment</a></em></strong></p>
<p>McMurtry is best known for writing like a cowboy. But friends said he <a href="https://www.vanityfair.com/style/2021/03/remembering-larry-mcmurtry?srsltid=AfmBOorgM7uiW5ngl-Y5xAhzCvHhxFcIT6Vu1VxKM3MdhLgIf9PSCfi8" class="external" target="_blank">gossiped like Jane Austen</a>.</p>
<p>Here, the inimitable matriarch Aurora Greenway&#8217;s suitors circle, clueless as Emma Woodhouse&#8217;s. And the failure of her daughter&#8217;s marriage is in part a class casualty. Emma&#8217;s man is a bit like Mr. Wickham, grifting his way around the periphery of academia as that sordid lieutenant did the British army.</p>
<p>But best of all here is the vexed mother/daughter relationship, which can echo Lizzy&#8217;s terms with her own mother. Watch two women with totally different value systems attempt to communicate, and see the bittersweet fallout.</p>
